# Privacy Policy – Bobby Discord Bot

**Last updated:** June 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how the Discord bot "Bobby" handles user data.

---

## 1. Data Collection

Bobby does not permanently store any user data.

The Bot may temporarily process the following data only to respond to commands:

* Discord user IDs
* Discord server IDs
* Message content sent to the Bot
* Command inputs

---

## 2. Data Storage

No user data is stored in a database or persistent storage.

Processed data is used only in memory during execution and is discarded immediately after use, unless required for temporary technical operation.

---

## 3. Third Parties

Bobby does not share user data with third parties.

If the Bot is configured to use a local AI system (e.g., self-hosted model), all processing is performed on infrastructure controlled by the Bot Owner.

---

## 4. Data Usage

Data is used exclusively to:

* Provide Bot functionality
* Process user commands
* Generate responses

---

## 5. Data Retention

No long-term retention of user data occurs.

---

## 6. Security

Reasonable technical measures are taken to protect the Bot’s infrastructure, but absolute security cannot be guaranteed.

---

## 7. Children’s Privacy

Users must comply with Discord’s minimum age requirements (13+ or local equivalent).

---

## 8. Changes

This Privacy Policy may be updated at any time. Continued use of the Bot implies acceptance of any changes.

---

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, you may contact the Bot Owner.
